    },
    "body": "\r\n### What changed\r\n\r\n**Renamed APIs**: `T.fadd2`/`T.fmul2` replaced with `T.add2`/`T.mul2`. Old backward-compat aliases (`fadd2`, `fmul2`, `fadd_f32x2`, `fmul_f32x2`, `fma_f32x2`) removed.\r\n\r\n**Expanded op surface**: Added 4 new packed x2 intrinsics (`T.sub2`, `T.max2`, `T.min2`, `T.abs2`) alongside the existing 3 (`add2`, `mul2`, `fma2`). All 7 ops are registered end-to-end: Python API, C++ op registration, CUDA codegen, HIP codegen, and C++ device templates.\r\n\r\n**Multi-dtype support**: All 7 ops now support 3 dtype families:\r\n- `float32x2` (CUDA `float2`) — uses PTX `.f32x2` instructions on SM100+, scalar fallback otherwise\r\n- `bfloat16x2` (CUDA `__nv_bfloat162`) — uses `__hadd2`/`__hsub2`/etc. on SM80+\r\n- `float16x2` (CUDA `__half2`) — uses `__hadd2`/`__hsub2`/etc. on SM53+\r\n\r\n### Auto-vectorization (`T.Parallel`) extended\r\n\r\n`PrintVecBinaryOp` now intercepts all 3 x2 types (not just `float32x2`) and all 5 binary ops (`+`/`-`/`*`/`min`/`max`), emitting `tl::*2` calls. Previously only `+` and `*` for `float32x2` were handled.\r\n\r\n### Tests: 54 tests (up from 6)\r\n\r\n| Category | Tests |\r\n|---|---|\r\n| Codegen: 7 ops x 3 dtypes (explicit intrinsics) | 21 |\r\n| Codegen: auto-vec `+`/`-`/`*` x float32 SM100 | 3 |\r\n| Codegen: auto-vec `+`/`-`/`*` x float32 SM80 (negative) | 3 |\r\n| Codegen: auto-vec `+`/`-`/`*` x bfloat16/float16 | 6 |\r\n| Correctness: 5 binary ops x 3 dtypes | 15 |\r\n| Correctness: fma2 x 3 dtypes | 3 |\r\n| Correctness: abs2 x 3 dtypes | 3 |\r\n\r\n\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  - Packed element-wise ops: add, sub, mul, min, max, abs (plus existing fused-multiply-add)\n  - New bfloat16x2 dtype supported\n\n* **Improvements**\n  - Extended packed x2 support to BFloat16x2 and Float16x2\n  - Improved CUDA/HIP code generation and auto-vectorization for packed x2 ops\n  - Better handling of mixed-size vector accesses to avoid incorrect lane normalization\n\n* **Tests**\n  - Expanded parametric tests and correctness checks for all packed x2 ops and dtypes\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
